messages.content: Stromatolites are special fossils that show how ancient cyanobacteria once lived in reefs built of these microbes.
Why do humans explore space according to the document?

Humans explore space to learn more about Earth's origins, the future, and the vast universe.  Scientists are also studying the possibility of past life on Mars and researching how to grow food in space to support future missions.
